!! Overview

''"Alles Leben ist Problemlösen"'' (All Life is Problem Solving) is a collection of essays and lectures by Karl Popper, often considered his intellectual legacy.

!! Key Points

@@Central Thesis: Problem-solving is the fundamental driving force of all life, from amoebas to Einstein.@@

''Evolution as Knowledge: Biological evolution is a trial-and-error process. Mutations are "conjectures," and natural selection is "refutation."''

Methodology: @@The core mechanism is Conjecture and Refutation. @@ We don't "prove" things; we eliminate errors.

Knowledge Growth: Science does not move toward absolute certainty but toward increasingly better approximations of truth by discarding false theories.